features: STYLE: The silver metal plaque buckle on this belt adds the perfect finishing touch with the Dickies logo, offering a different and casual look with jeans or trousers.
CASUAL: Being a fabric belt, this style will add a unique touch to any outfit. Whether you are out with friends, skating the streets, or working on a project, this is a dependable casual belt.

SIZING: This fabric belt is one size fits all. The cut-to-fit construction lets you customize your belt to ensure you have the perfect fit every time. Strap measures 1.5 inches wide and 50 inches long.
GENDER NEUTRAL: Designed for all, this cotton web belt is meant to be worn by anyone, anywhere, anytime. With it's versatile use the options are endless
body.description: Dickies men's belts are the perfect item to wear with your cool looking outfits. These cotton web belts are easy and comfortable for everyday wears.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks good, does the job
reviews.reviewText: good military belt, I use it for work and I usually keep my Otterbox connected to it. It sags easy if its not tightened to hold the belt, but when its tight, it holds js about anything.No rips or loose threading though I use it daily! I would recommend for light work wear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Dickies Men's Cotton Web Belt with Military Logo Buckle worth the price.
reviews.reviewText: Fits waists up to 49 inches. If your size is smaller, just carefully cut off what you don't need. Should last years. Several colors including black. Once the simplicity of this "military" style belt is mastered, you will wear it before other belts. Good for you for buying this belt. Nice Dickies logo on buckle, looks sharp. Dickies belt loops are made for this belt.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Use the logo style as in the 1.25 inch black canvas belt but keep the same buckle style.
reviews.reviewText: The belt was really nice. I like the buckle style also but I had to return it because it was a 1.5 inch wide belt and it wouldn't fit thru the Dickies pants loop.Also, should change the logo style like the one used in the black 1.25 inch black belt buckle. It looks quieter and classier. The size of the logo installed on the 1.5 inch buckle should be as in the 1.25 inch buckle. Honestly, I maybe would've kept the belt if the logo style was metal (as previously mentioned) like the 1.25 inch belt.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Buckle kept falling off (into toilet!!) but I was able to fix it.
reviews.reviewText: I had higher hopes for this belt, but was able to fix its shortcomings pretty easily. The buckle would often fall off when I was undoing it in the bathroom. Twice it fell into the toilet below...once at a client's house, and they hadn't flushed it!! Luckily, I had one of those telescoping, magnetic pick-up tools in my truck toolbox, so I was able to retrieve it without things getting too gross. I fixed it by cutting off about an inch off the buckle end of the webbing, and using that to increase the thickness of the belt where the buckle's sawtooth "jaw' clamps come down. That made the buckle/fabric joint much more tight. No more flying buckles after that! Another problem was that the little roller that slides in the buckle slot sometimes would get hung up and not go back into its little resting slot....also very annoying. I fixed that by prying the slot apart just a little bit using a flat blade screwdriver. From this point on, I am hoping its smooth sailing!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My son was absolutely thrilled!
reviews.reviewText: This is a gorgeous belt. IF a man is big, he will need to buy an additional larger belt. But the buckle is beautiful and really a standout. It is adjustable, so you can buy an additional belt easily. It was a stocking stuffer and he just loved it. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Had to buy a second and might need a third🤦🏼‍♀️
reviews.reviewText: My youngest stole my oldest daughters because she liked it so much so I had to buy a second and now I might have to get a third for my son who is suddenly taking turns kidnapping my daughters belts…I do like that you can trim it down to resize the belt so there isn’t too much slack. I don’t like that it’s hard to get the clamp to hold on to the side you trim on the belt buckle. I yanked at it to make sure it would hold once I took off the white tag that was sticking out from under the clamp and it took two or three times before it would hold the belt. Haven’t had any issues ever since.I will say the only weird thing I noticed was that the first one I purchased about a year ago has a little bit of a blackish look to the background of the buckle and the one I just recently purchased is SILVER silver. No black background at all. Not a big deal but it was unexpected since I did click buy again and was slightly thrown off when I got it and the color was different
I love it. You can regulate the size which is great!I would definitely recommend it
